        "subject": "LU-9091 tests: use upstream units for proc settings",
        "message": "LU-9091 tests: use upstream units for proc settings\n\nThe work for LU-7734 was written long before the linux kernel\nintroduced string helpers. This patch uses the units approved\nof upstream instead of the ones currently supported, M,K,G etc.\nThis will show that the current work by LU-7734 is written such\nthat it will not see a difference between the upstream units and\nwhat is currently supported.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity envdefinitions=\"ONLY=101g\"\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=conf-sanity envdefinitions=\"ONLY=32\"\n\nChange-Id: I62ea4fc2151492d0ddd20757ca877fd90aafdae0\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
